The National EducationHealthand Allied Workers Union is taking the Health Department to court. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Labour Court is expected to hear the National Education Health and Allied Workers Union's (Nehawu) bid to force the government to provide workers with protective gear against the coronavirus. READ: Unions drag government to court The union launched a bid against Labour Minister Thulasi Nxesi, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize and nine provincial health MECs. It wants them to comply with the Occupational Health and Safety Act. READ:Â Nehawu fights for protective equipment The union says there aren't enough masks, gloves and sanitiser for health workers at the forefront of the coronavirus pandemic. So far, the virus has claimed 12 lives and infected 1686 people in South Africa.